				<a name="109469564845601463"></a> 
				I have to say, I am honestly impressed with people here. Although comments here and there cause me to go on my long winded, boring rants, which probably come out of my own personal boredom, I am generally pleased with things I read. Well except for the fact that you think Murdoch owns the media, in reality he owns a 30% share in a company called NewsCorp, which is one of four companies that owns pretty much everything. Don't worry, I am not disputing the fact that the flow of information is severely choked, with that we can both agree. <br /><br />This is one of those times I will throw my age into play. It is very promising when I see INTELLIGENT thought here on the things that are going on around us. I can definitely say you all pay much more attention at your age than 75% of the people I knew at that age. It is also very nice to see that unlike my parents, and my friend's parents, that it is not all one sided, follow the pied piper, my party is my team bullshit.<br /><br />Anyway, Moore is a prick! LOL... Actually I find it funny J when I followed that link to the USA Today piece. They hired Ann Coulter to cover the Democratic Convention, and then fired her because she was "too devisive", and then proceeded a month later to hire Moore to cover the Republican Convention. You would think they could at least pretend to be the 1st Amendment carrying, UNBIASED, defenders of truth that the press was intended to be. I would think the editor of USA Today might possibly think with Moore's movie that it may be a conflict of interest on his part. Oh well, a fantasy of a bygone age I guess.<br /><br />Do you think the spirit of Orwell is looking down thinking "damn I was close"?<br />
				<div class="byline"><a href="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/2004/09/zing.php#109469564845601463" title="permanent link">#</a> posted by <a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3576614">TuuKAholiC</a> @ 10:07 PM</div>
				<span class="item-control admin-800438703 pid-699792531"><a style="border:none;" href="http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.do?blogID=6900590&postID=109469564845601463" title="Delete Comment" ><span class="delete-comment-icon">&nbsp;</span></a></span>
