			<div class="blogComment">
				<a name="109469768576257296"></a> 
				You know, after reading the rest of that Moore article, I really have to ask myself how it is Moore feels justified using his 1st Amendment right to rail against those who actually do something to defend it? This elitist piece of waste, sits in his Ivory Tower, taking money hand over fist from the very American people he personally calls "STUPID" in interview after interview. Us pathetic peasants below him, we are all so unrefined and ignorant. <br /><br />He may be on to something, after all, he has made quite a bit of Capitalist cash shitting on this society and espousing his Socialist beliefs. I would love to live in his dream of a world, a world where we are all completely equal, a world like the Soviet Union and other previously Eastern Bloc nations where all were equal.... oh yeah, everyone but a select few who are chosen to run the place for all of us idiots that can't make decisions for ourselves. <br /><br />And for all of the hard work these people put themselves through, running things for the rest of us idiots who couldn't possibly be trusted to make decisions regarding our own future, they of course get to have a litte... a LOT extra. Palaces, gourmet food, works of art, automobiles, books of poetry that the people cannot have as it may actually provoke intellectual thought, music, and many other amenities. <br /><br />This while the people that worked in their industries had to wait in line an entire day for a loaf of bread and were rationed out one roll of toilet paper, per person, per month. That automobile I mentioned, well if a good Socialist/Communist citizen worked hard for the Motherland, well after 30 or 40 years that could request to be put on a waiting list for a nice little Citroen or maybe even a Fiat. <br /><br />The line in this list of course usually meant in 20 or so years you would get your car, unless of course you died in the miserable industry you slaved in to keep the Party...um Protectors of the Motherland in their nice lives. Good God I completely understand their plight, after all, my position on the waiting list for Redskins tickets may net me a pair by the time I am 60 or 70... Oh the oppressive horror, I think I will make documentary detailing my miserable existence....<br /><br />I know a few people here think a Socialist Utopia would be a grand society. You are right, in a vacum. The psychology of human nature is what destroys it, and what causes capitalism to thrive. There always will be a segment of society that will take advatage of a situation where they can do little or no work, and still get an equal amount. Greed is the key ingredient that would subvert the Socialist Utopia. <br /><br />If you don't agree with me, do some reference on the Mayflower, the Plymouth Colony, and why we REALLY celebrate Thanksgiving. Greed is why Capitalism works, and why it thrives, pushing technological advancements, and why Socialism's inherent non competetive nature in the end stagnates knowledge and suffocates progress. Greed is not always a bad word, its accepted definition is what makes it all bad, all of the time. Greed is pasion, it is what drives us to make a better mousetrap than the guy next door did, and it is why neighbors get into pissing contests with their light displays at Christmas.. LOL<br /><br /><A HREF="http://www.blogger.com/r?http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mises.org%2Ffullstory.aspx%3Fcontrol%3D1571">The Idiotic Irony of Michael Moore's Socialist Dream</A><br />
